ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project focuses on building an end-to-end Credit Card Fraud Detection system using Machine Learning.
The model is trained on imbalanced transactional data and deployed using Streamlit to provide real-time fraud prediction.

The system uses an Extra Trees Classifier, which performed best compared to other models due to its ability to handle complex patterns and imbalanced data effectively.

ğŸ¯ Objectives

Detect fraudulent credit card transactions accurately

Handle highly imbalanced datasets

Build a reliable and interpretable ML model

Deploy the trained model as an interactive web application

Enable real-time prediction for new transactions

ğŸ§  Machine Learning Approach
âœ” Data Challenges

Severe class imbalance (fraud cases are very rare)

High dimensional numerical features

Need for strong recall on fraud class

âœ” Techniques Used

StandardScaler for feature scaling

SMOTE (Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique) to balance data

Extra Trees Classifier for robust classification

Proper evaluation using Recall, F1-score, ROC-AUC

